- `x = x`: The element we're checking if it's in the support.
- `#v[true, false]`: This is the vector `⟨true, false⟩` of type `Vector Bool 2`.

The definition of `HasUniformSelect!.uniformSelect!` is `(cont : Type u) (β : outParam Type) → cont → ProbComp β`. So for our specific case:
`@OracleComp.HasUniformSelect!.uniformSelect! (Vector Bool 2) Bool (OracleComp.hasUniformSelectVector Bool 1) #v[true, false]` is a `ProbComp Bool` representing the probability distribution of selecting an element from `#v[true, false]`.

The `support` of a `ProbComp β` is a subset of `β`. For a probability distribution `P` over `Bool`, `P.support` is the set of `b : Bool` such that `Pr[= b | P] > 0`.

In our case, `P = @OracleComp.HasUniformSelect!.uniformSelect! (Vector Bool 2) Bool (OracleComp.hasUniformSelectVector Bool 1) #v[true, false]`. The instance `hα` provides the definition of `uniformSelect!` for `Vector α (n+1)`. Looking at the definition in the context:
